{"id":"231","title":"Power of Two","difficulty":"Easy","content":"<p>Given an integer <code>n</code>, return <em><code>true</code> if it is a power of two. Otherwise, return <code>false</code></em>.</p>\n\n<p>An integer <code>n</code> is a power of two, if there exists an integer <code>x</code> such that <code>n == 2<sup>x</sup></code>.</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong class=\"example\">Example 1:</strong></p>\n\n<pre>\n<strong>Input:</strong> n = 1\n<strong>Output:</strong> true\n<strong>Explanation: </strong>2<sup>0</sup> = 1\n</pre>\n\n<p><strong class=\"example\">Example 2:</strong></p>\n\n<pre>\n<strong>Input:</strong> n = 16\n<strong>Output:</strong> true\n<strong>Explanation: </strong>2<sup>4</sup> = 16\n</pre>\n\n<p><strong class=\"example\">Example 3:</strong></p>\n\n<pre>\n<strong>Input:</strong> n = 3\n<strong>Output:</strong> false\n</pre>\n\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>Constraints:</strong></p>\n\n<ul>\n\t<li><code>-2<sup>31</sup> &lt;= n &lt;= 2<sup>31</sup> - 1</code></li>\n</ul>\n\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<strong>Follow up:</strong> Could you solve it without loops/recursion?","tags":["Math","Bit Manipulation","Recursion"],"java_snippet":"class Solution {\n    public boolean isPowerOfTwo(int n) {\n        \n    }\n}","solution":"<div class=\"flex flex-col w-full\" style=\"position: relative;\"><div class=\"mYe_l WRmCx\"><h2 class=\"group/heading relative\" id=\"solution\" level=\"2\"><a aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"!text-sd-muted-foreground absolute right-full top-1/2 -translate-y-1/2 cursor-pointer pr-0.5 text-xs opacity-0 group-hover/heading:opacity-100\" href=\"#solution\" tabindex=\"-1\"><div class=\"relative text-[12px] leading-[normal] p-[1px] before:block before:h-3 before:w-3\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"svg-inline--fa fa-link absolute left-1/2 top-1/2 h-[1em] -translate-x-1/2 -translate-y-1/2 align-[-0.125em]\" data-icon=\"link\" data-prefix=\"fas\" focusable=\"false\" role=\"img\" spacing=\"square\" viewbox=\"0 0 640 512\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\"><path d=\"M579.8 267.7c56.5-56.5 56.5-148 0-204.5c-50-50-128.8-56.5-186.3-15.4l-1.6 1.1c-14.4 10.3-17.7 30.3-7.4 44.6s30.3 17.7 44.6 7.4l1.6-1.1c32.1-22.9 76-19.3 103.8 8.6c31.5 31.5 31.5 82.5 0 114L422.3 334.8c-31.5 31.5-82.5 31.5-114 0c-27.9-27.9-31.5-71.8-8.6-103.8l1.1-1.6c10.3-14.4 6.9-34.4-7.4-44.6s-34.4-6.9-44.6 7.4l-1.1 1.6C206.5 251.2 213 330 263 380c56.5 56.5 148 56.5 204.5 0L579.8 267.7zM60.2 244.3c-56.5 56.5-56.5 148 0 204.5c50 50 128.8 56.5 186.3 15.4l1.6-1.1c14.4-10.3 17.7-30.3 7.4-44.6s-30.3-17.7-44.6-7.4l-1.6 1.1c-32.1 22.9-76 19.3-103.8-8.6C74 372 74 321 105.5 289.5L217.7 177.2c31.5-31.5 82.5-31.5 114 0c27.9 27.9 31.5 71.8 8.6 103.9l-1.1 1.6c-10.3 14.4-6.9 34.4 7.4 44.6s34.4 6.9 44.6-7.4l1.1-1.6C433.5 260.8 427 182 377 132c-56.5-56.5-148-56.5-204.5 0L60.2 244.3z\" fill=\"currentColor\"></path></svg></div></a>Solution</h2>\n<hr/>\n<h3 class=\"group/heading relative\" id=\"overview\" level=\"3\"><a aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"!text-sd-muted-foreground absolute right-full top-1/2 -translate-y-1/2 cursor-pointer pr-0.5 text-xs opacity-0 group-hover/heading:opacity-100\" href=\"#overview\" tabindex=\"-1\"><div class=\"relative text-[12px] leading-[normal] p-[1px] before:block before:h-3 before:w-3\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"svg-inline--fa fa-link absolute left-1/2 top-1/2 h-[1em] -translate-x-1/2 -translate-y-1/2 align-[-0.125em]\" data-icon=\"link\" data-prefix=\"fas\" focusable=\"false\" role=\"img\" spacing=\"square\" viewbox=\"0 0 640 512\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\"><path d=\"M579.8 267.7c56.5-56.5 56.5-148 0-204.5c-50-50-128.8-56.5-186.3-15.4l-1.6 1.1c-14.4 10.3-17.7 30.3-7.4 44.6s30.3 17.7 44.6 7.4l1.6-1.1c32.1-22.9 76-19.3 103.8 8.6c31.5 31.5 31.5 82.5 0 114L422.3 334.8c-31.5 31.5-82.5 31.5-114 0c-27.9-27.9-31.5-71.8-8.6-103.8l1.1-1.6c10.3-14.4 6.9-34.4-7.4-44.6s-34.4-6.9-44.6 7.4l-1.1 1.6C206.5 251.2 213 330 263 380c56.5 56.5 148 56.5 204.5 0L579.8 267.7zM60.2 244.3c-56.5 56.5-56.5 148 0 204.5c50 50 128.8 56.5 186.3 15.4l1.6-1.1c14.4-10.3 17.7-30.3 7.4-44.6s-30.3-17.7-44.6-7.4l-1.6 1.1c-32.1 22.9-76 19.3-103.8-8.6C74 372 74 321 105.5 289.5L217.7 177.2c31.5-31.5 82.5-31.5 114 0c27.9 27.9 31.5 71.8 8.6 103.9l-1.1 1.6c-10.3 14.4-6.9 34.4 7.4 44.6s34.4 6.9 44.6-7.4l1.1-1.6C433.5 260.8 427 182 377 132c-56.5-56.5-148-56.5-204.5 0L60.2 244.3z\" fill=\"currentColor\"></path></svg></div></a>Overview</h3>\n<p>A intuitive way to check the power of two is to check whether we can divide the number repeatedly by 2 until we reach 1. If at any point the number isn't divisible by 2, then it isn't a power of two.</p>\n<p>This solution runs in <span class=\"math math-inline\"><span class=\"katex\"><span aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"katex-html\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height: 1em; vertical-align: -0.25em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathcal\" style=\"margin-right: 0.02778em;\">O</span><span class=\"mopen\">(</span><span class=\"mop\">lo<span style=\"margin-right: 0.01389em;\">g</span></span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right: 0.1667em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right: 0.10903em;\">N</span><span class=\"mclose\">)</span></span></span></span></span> time because we divide the number by 2 at each step, and it takes approximately <span class=\"math math-inline\"><span class=\"katex\"><span aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"katex-html\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height: 1em; vertical-align: -0.25em;\"></span><span class=\"mop\"><span class=\"mop\">lo<span style=\"margin-right: 0.01389em;\">g</span></span><span class=\"msupsub\"><span class=\"vlist-t vlist-t2\"><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height: 0.207em;\"><span style=\"top: -2.4559em; margin-right: 0.05em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height: 2.7em;\"></span><span class=\"sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight\"><span class=\"mord mtight\">2</span></span></span></span><span class=\"vlist-s\">​</span></span><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height: 0.2441em;\"><span></span></span></span></span></span></span><span class=\"mopen\">(</span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right: 0.10903em;\">N</span><span class=\"mclose\">)</span></span></span></span></span> divisions before we reach 1 (or realize it's not possible).</p>\n<pre><code>class Solution {\npublic:\n    bool isPowerOfTwo(int n) {\n        if (n == 0) return false;\n        while (n % 2 == 0) n /= 2;\n        return n == 1;\n    }\n};</code></pre>\n<p>Instead, the problem will be solved in <span class=\"math math-inline\"><span class=\"katex\"><span aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"katex-html\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height: 1em; vertical-align: -0.25em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathcal\" style=\"margin-right: 0.02778em;\">O</span><span class=\"mopen\">(</span><span class=\"mord\">1</span><span class=\"mclose\">)</span></span></span></span></span> time with the help of bitwise operators. The idea is to discuss such bitwise tricks as</p>\n<ul>\n<li>\n<p>How to get / isolate the rightmost 1-bit : <code>n &amp; (-n)</code>.</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>How to turn off (= set to 0) the rightmost 1-bit : <code>n &amp; (n - 1)</code>.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p>These tricks are often used as something obvious in more complex bit-manipulation solutions, like for <a href=\"https://leetcode.com/articles/n-queens-ii/\" target=\"_blank\">N Queens problem</a>, and it's important to recognize them to understand what is going on.<br/>\n<br/><br/>\n<br/></p>\n<hr/>\n<h4 id=\"intuition\">Intuition</h4>\n<p>The idea behind both solutions will be the same: a power of two in binary representation is one 1-bit, followed by some zeros:</p>\n<p><span class=\"math math-inline\"><span class=\"katex\"><span aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"katex-html\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height: 0.6444em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\">1</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right: 0.2778em;\"></span><span class=\"mrel\">=</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right: 0.2778em;\"></span></span><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height: 1em; vertical-align: -0.25em;\"></span><span class=\"mopen\">(</span><span class=\"mord\">00000001</span><span class=\"mclose\"><span class=\"mclose\">)</span><span class=\"msupsub\"><span class=\"vlist-t vlist-t2\"><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height: 0.3011em;\"><span style=\"top: -2.55em; margin-left: 0em; margin-right: 0.05em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height: 2.7em;\"></span><span class=\"sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight\"><span class=\"mord mtight\">2</span></span></span></span><span class=\"vlist-s\">​</span></span><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height: 0.15em;\"><span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></p>\n<p><span class=\"math math-inline\"><span class=\"katex\"><span aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"katex-html\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height: 0.6444em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\">2</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right: 0.2778em;\"></span><span class=\"mrel\">=</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right: 0.2778em;\"></span></span><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height: 1em; vertical-align: -0.25em;\"></span><span class=\"mopen\">(</span><span class=\"mord\">00000010</span><span class=\"mclose\"><span class=\"mclose\">)</span><span class=\"msupsub\"><span class=\"vlist-t vlist-t2\"><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height: 0.3011em;\"><span style=\"top: -2.55em; margin-left: 0em; margin-right: 0.05em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height: 2.7em;\"></span><span class=\"sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight\"><span class=\"mord mtight\">2</span></span></span></span><span class=\"vlist-s\">​</span></span><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height: 0.15em;\"><span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></p>\n<p><span class=\"math math-inline\"><span class=\"katex\"><span aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"katex-html\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height: 0.6444em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\">4</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right: 0.2778em;\"></span><span class=\"mrel\">=</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right: 0.2778em;\"></span></span><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height: 1em; vertical-align: -0.25em;\"></span><span class=\"mopen\">(</span><span class=\"mord\">00000100</span><span class=\"mclose\"><span class=\"mclose\">)</span><span class=\"msupsub\"><span class=\"vlist-t vlist-t2\"><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height: 0.3011em;\"><span style=\"top: -2.55em; margin-left: 0em; margin-right: 0.05em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height: 2.7em;\"></span><span class=\"sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight\"><span class=\"mord mtight\">2</span></span></span></span><span class=\"vlist-s\">​</span></span><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height: 0.15em;\"><span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></p>\n<p><span class=\"math math-inline\"><span class=\"katex\"><span aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"katex-html\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height: 0.6444em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\">8</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right: 0.2778em;\"></span><span class=\"mrel\">=</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right: 0.2778em;\"></span></span><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height: 1em; vertical-align: -0.25em;\"></span><span class=\"mopen\">(</span><span class=\"mord\">00001000</span><span class=\"mclose\"><span class=\"mclose\">)</span><span class=\"msupsub\"><span class=\"vlist-t vlist-t2\"><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height: 0.3011em;\"><span style=\"top: -2.55em; margin-left: 0em; margin-right: 0.05em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height: 2.7em;\"></span><span class=\"sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight\"><span class=\"mord mtight\">2</span></span></span></span><span class=\"vlist-s\">​</span></span><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height: 0.15em;\"><span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></p>\n<p>A number that is not a power of two has more than one 1-bit in its binary representation:</p>\n<p><span class=\"math math-inline\"><span class=\"katex\"><span aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"katex-html\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height: 0.6444em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\">3</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right: 0.2778em;\"></span><span class=\"mrel\">=</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right: 0.2778em;\"></span></span><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height: 1em; vertical-align: -0.25em;\"></span><span class=\"mopen\">(</span><span class=\"mord\">00000011</span><span class=\"mclose\"><span class=\"mclose\">)</span><span class=\"msupsub\"><span class=\"vlist-t vlist-t2\"><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height: 0.3011em;\"><span style=\"top: -2.55em; margin-left: 0em; margin-right: 0.05em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height: 2.7em;\"></span><span class=\"sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight\"><span class=\"mord mtight\">2</span></span></span></span><span class=\"vlist-s\">​</span></span><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height: 0.15em;\"><span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></p>\n<p><span class=\"math math-inline\"><span class=\"katex\"><span aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"katex-html\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height: 0.6444em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\">5</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right: 0.2778em;\"></span><span class=\"mrel\">=</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right: 0.2778em;\"></span></span><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height: 1em; vertical-align: -0.25em;\"></span><span class=\"mopen\">(</span><span class=\"mord\">00000101</span><span class=\"mclose\"><span class=\"mclose\">)</span><span class=\"msupsub\"><span class=\"vlist-t vlist-t2\"><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height: 0.3011em;\"><span style=\"top: -2.55em; margin-left: 0em; margin-right: 0.05em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height: 2.7em;\"></span><span class=\"sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight\"><span class=\"mord mtight\">2</span></span></span></span><span class=\"vlist-s\">​</span></span><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height: 0.15em;\"><span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></p>\n<p><span class=\"math math-inline\"><span class=\"katex\"><span aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"katex-html\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height: 0.6444em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\">6</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right: 0.2778em;\"></span><span class=\"mrel\">=</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right: 0.2778em;\"></span></span><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height: 1em; vertical-align: -0.25em;\"></span><span class=\"mopen\">(</span><span class=\"mord\">00000110</span><span class=\"mclose\"><span class=\"mclose\">)</span><span class=\"msupsub\"><span class=\"vlist-t vlist-t2\"><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height: 0.3011em;\"><span style=\"top: -2.55em; margin-left: 0em; margin-right: 0.05em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height: 2.7em;\"></span><span class=\"sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight\"><span class=\"mord mtight\">2</span></span></span></span><span class=\"vlist-s\">​</span></span><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height: 0.15em;\"><span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></p>\n<p><span class=\"math math-inline\"><span class=\"katex\"><span aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"katex-html\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height: 0.6444em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\">7</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right: 0.2778em;\"></span><span class=\"mrel\">=</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right: 0.2778em;\"></span></span><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height: 1em; vertical-align: -0.25em;\"></span><span class=\"mopen\">(</span><span class=\"mord\">00000111</span><span class=\"mclose\"><span class=\"mclose\">)</span><span class=\"msupsub\"><span class=\"vlist-t vlist-t2\"><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height: 0.3011em;\"><span style=\"top: -2.55em; margin-left: 0em; margin-right: 0.05em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height: 2.7em;\"></span><span class=\"sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight\"><span class=\"mord mtight\">2</span></span></span></span><span class=\"vlist-s\">​</span></span><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height: 0.15em;\"><span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></p>\n<p>The only exception is 0, which should be treated separately.<br/>\n<br/><br/>\n<br/></p>\n<hr/>\n<h3 class=\"group/heading relative\" id=\"approach-1-bitwise-operators-get-the-rightmost-1-bit\" level=\"3\"><a aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"!text-sd-muted-foreground absolute right-full top-1/2 -translate-y-1/2 cursor-pointer pr-0.5 text-xs opacity-0 group-hover/heading:opacity-100\" href=\"#approach-1-bitwise-operators-get-the-rightmost-1-bit\" tabindex=\"-1\"><div class=\"relative text-[12px] leading-[normal] p-[1px] before:block before:h-3 before:w-3\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"svg-inline--fa fa-link absolute left-1/2 top-1/2 h-[1em] -translate-x-1/2 -translate-y-1/2 align-[-0.125em]\" data-icon=\"link\" data-prefix=\"fas\" focusable=\"false\" role=\"img\" spacing=\"square\" viewbox=\"0 0 640 512\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\"><path d=\"M579.8 267.7c56.5-56.5 56.5-148 0-204.5c-50-50-128.8-56.5-186.3-15.4l-1.6 1.1c-14.4 10.3-17.7 30.3-7.4 44.6s30.3 17.7 44.6 7.4l1.6-1.1c32.1-22.9 76-19.3 103.8 8.6c31.5 31.5 31.5 82.5 0 114L422.3 334.8c-31.5 31.5-82.5 31.5-114 0c-27.9-27.9-31.5-71.8-8.6-103.8l1.1-1.6c10.3-14.4 6.9-34.4-7.4-44.6s-34.4-6.9-44.6 7.4l-1.1 1.6C206.5 251.2 213 330 263 380c56.5 56.5 148 56.5 204.5 0L579.8 267.7zM60.2 244.3c-56.5 56.5-56.5 148 0 204.5c50 50 128.8 56.5 186.3 15.4l1.6-1.1c14.4-10.3 17.7-30.3 7.4-44.6s-30.3-17.7-44.6-7.4l-1.6 1.1c-32.1 22.9-76 19.3-103.8-8.6C74 372 74 321 105.5 289.5L217.7 177.2c31.5-31.5 82.5-31.5 114 0c27.9 27.9 31.5 71.8 8.6 103.9l-1.1 1.6c-10.3 14.4-6.9 34.4 7.4 44.6s34.4 6.9 44.6-7.4l1.1-1.6C433.5 260.8 427 182 377 132c-56.5-56.5-148-56.5-204.5 0L60.2 244.3z\" fill=\"currentColor\"></path></svg></div></a>Approach 1: Bitwise Operators: Get the Rightmost 1-bit</h3>\n<p><strong>Get/Isolate the Rightmost 1-bit</strong></p>\n<p>Let's first discuss why <code>n &amp; (-n)</code> is a way to keep the rightmost 1-bit and to set all the other bits to 0.</p>\n<p>Basically, that works because of <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Two%27s_complement\" target=\"_blank\">two's complement</a>. In two's complement notation <span class=\"math math-inline\"><span class=\"katex\"><span aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"katex-html\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height: 0.6667em; vertical-align: -0.0833em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\">−</span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">n</span></span></span></span></span> is the same as <span class=\"math math-inline\"><span class=\"katex\"><span aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"katex-html\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height: 0.6667em; vertical-align: -0.0833em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\">¬</span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">n</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right: 0.2222em;\"></span><span class=\"mbin\">+</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right: 0.2222em;\"></span></span><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height: 0.6444em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\">1</span></span></span></span></span>. In other words, to compute <span class=\"math math-inline\"><span class=\"katex\"><span aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"katex-html\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height: 0.6667em; vertical-align: -0.0833em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\">−</span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">n</span></span></span></span></span> one has to revert all bits in <span class=\"math math-inline\"><span class=\"katex\"><span aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"katex-html\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height: 0.4306em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">n</span></span></span></span></span> and then add 1 to the result.</p>\n<p>Adding 1 to <span class=\"math math-inline\"><span class=\"katex\"><span aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"katex-html\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height: 0.4306em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\">¬</span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">n</span></span></span></span></span> in binary representation means to carry that 1-bit till the rightmost 0-bit in <span class=\"math math-inline\"><span class=\"katex\"><span aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"katex-html\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height: 0.4306em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\">¬</span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">n</span></span></span></span></span> and to set all the lower bits to zero. Note, that the rightmost 0-bit in <span class=\"math math-inline\"><span class=\"katex\"><span aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"katex-html\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height: 0.4306em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\">¬</span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">n</span></span></span></span></span> corresponds to the rightmost 1-bit in <span class=\"math math-inline\"><span class=\"katex\"><span aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"katex-html\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height: 0.4306em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">n</span></span></span></span></span>.</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>In summary, <span class=\"math math-inline\"><span class=\"katex\"><span aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"katex-html\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height: 0.6667em; vertical-align: -0.0833em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\">−</span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">n</span></span></span></span></span> is the same as <span class=\"math math-inline\"><span class=\"katex\"><span aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"katex-html\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height: 0.6667em; vertical-align: -0.0833em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\">¬</span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">n</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right: 0.2222em;\"></span><span class=\"mbin\">+</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right: 0.2222em;\"></span></span><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height: 0.6444em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\">1</span></span></span></span></span>. This operation reverts all bits of n except the rightmost 1-bit.</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p></p>\n<p>Hence, n and -n have just one bit in common - the rightmost 1-bit. That means that <code>n &amp; (-n)</code> would keep that rightmost 1-bit and set all the other bits to 0.</p>\n<p></p>\n<p><strong>Detect Power of Two</strong></p>\n<p>So let's do <code>n &amp; (-n)</code> to keep the rightmost 1-bit and set all the other bits to zero. As discussed above, for the power of two, it would result in <code>n</code> itself, since a power of two contains just one 1-bit.</p>\n<p>Other numbers have more than 1-bit in their binary representation and hence for them <code>n &amp; (-n)</code> would not be equal to <code>n</code> itself.</p>\n<p>Hence a number is a power of two if <code>n &amp; (-n) == n</code>.</p>\n<p></p>\n<p><strong>Implementation</strong></p>\n<pre><code>class Solution {\npublic:\n    bool isPowerOfTwo(int n) {\n        if (n &lt;= 0)\n            return false;\n        return (n &amp; (-n)) == n;\n    }\n};</code></pre>\n<p><strong>Complexity Analysis</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li>\n<p>Time complexity: <span class=\"math math-inline\"><span class=\"katex\"><span aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"katex-html\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height: 1em; vertical-align: -0.25em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathcal\" style=\"margin-right: 0.02778em;\">O</span><span class=\"mopen\">(</span><span class=\"mord\">1</span><span class=\"mclose\">)</span></span></span></span></span>.</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>Space complexity: <span class=\"math math-inline\"><span class=\"katex\"><span aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"katex-html\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height: 1em; vertical-align: -0.25em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathcal\" style=\"margin-right: 0.02778em;\">O</span><span class=\"mopen\">(</span><span class=\"mord\">1</span><span class=\"mclose\">)</span></span></span></span></span>.</p>\n<br/>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<br/>\n<hr/>\n<h3 class=\"group/heading relative\" id=\"approach-2-bitwise-operators-turn-off-the-rightmost-1-bit\" level=\"3\"><a aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"!text-sd-muted-foreground absolute right-full top-1/2 -translate-y-1/2 cursor-pointer pr-0.5 text-xs opacity-0 group-hover/heading:opacity-100\" href=\"#approach-2-bitwise-operators-turn-off-the-rightmost-1-bit\" tabindex=\"-1\"><div class=\"relative text-[12px] leading-[normal] p-[1px] before:block before:h-3 before:w-3\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"svg-inline--fa fa-link absolute left-1/2 top-1/2 h-[1em] -translate-x-1/2 -translate-y-1/2 align-[-0.125em]\" data-icon=\"link\" data-prefix=\"fas\" focusable=\"false\" role=\"img\" spacing=\"square\" viewbox=\"0 0 640 512\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\"><path d=\"M579.8 267.7c56.5-56.5 56.5-148 0-204.5c-50-50-128.8-56.5-186.3-15.4l-1.6 1.1c-14.4 10.3-17.7 30.3-7.4 44.6s30.3 17.7 44.6 7.4l1.6-1.1c32.1-22.9 76-19.3 103.8 8.6c31.5 31.5 31.5 82.5 0 114L422.3 334.8c-31.5 31.5-82.5 31.5-114 0c-27.9-27.9-31.5-71.8-8.6-103.8l1.1-1.6c10.3-14.4 6.9-34.4-7.4-44.6s-34.4-6.9-44.6 7.4l-1.1 1.6C206.5 251.2 213 330 263 380c56.5 56.5 148 56.5 204.5 0L579.8 267.7zM60.2 244.3c-56.5 56.5-56.5 148 0 204.5c50 50 128.8 56.5 186.3 15.4l1.6-1.1c14.4-10.3 17.7-30.3 7.4-44.6s-30.3-17.7-44.6-7.4l-1.6 1.1c-32.1 22.9-76 19.3-103.8-8.6C74 372 74 321 105.5 289.5L217.7 177.2c31.5-31.5 82.5-31.5 114 0c27.9 27.9 31.5 71.8 8.6 103.9l-1.1 1.6c-10.3 14.4-6.9 34.4 7.4 44.6s34.4 6.9 44.6-7.4l1.1-1.6C433.5 260.8 427 182 377 132c-56.5-56.5-148-56.5-204.5 0L60.2 244.3z\" fill=\"currentColor\"></path></svg></div></a>Approach 2: Bitwise operators: Turn off the Rightmost 1-bit</h3>\n<p><strong>Turn off the Rightmost 1-bit</strong></p>\n<p>Let's first discuss why <code>n &amp; (n - 1)</code> is a way to set the rightmost 1-bit to zero.</p>\n<p>To subtract 1 means to change the rightmost 1-bit to 0 and to set all the lower bits to 1.</p>\n<p>Now AND operator: the rightmost 1-bit will be turned off because <code>1 &amp; 0 = 0</code>, and all the lower bits as well.</p>\n<p></p>\n<p><strong>Detect Power of Two</strong></p>\n<p>The solution is straightforward:</p>\n<ol>\n<li data-length=\"1\">\n<p>Power of two has just one 1-bit.</p>\n</li>\n<li data-length=\"1\">\n<p><code>n &amp; (n - 1)</code> sets this 1-bit to zero, and hence one has to verify if the result is zero <code>n &amp; (n - 1) == 0</code>.</p>\n</li>\n</ol>\n<p></p>\n<p><strong>Implementation</strong></p>\n<pre><code>class Solution {\n  public:\n  bool isPowerOfTwo(int n) {\n    if (n &lt;= 0) return false;\n    return (n &amp; (n - 1)) == 0;\n  }\n};</code></pre>\n<p><strong>Complexity Analysis</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li>\n<p>Time complexity: <span class=\"math math-inline\"><span class=\"katex\"><span aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"katex-html\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height: 1em; vertical-align: -0.25em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathcal\" style=\"margin-right: 0.02778em;\">O</span><span class=\"mopen\">(</span><span class=\"mord\">1</span><span class=\"mclose\">)</span></span></span></span></span>.</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>Space complexity: <span class=\"math math-inline\"><span class=\"katex\"><span aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"katex-html\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height: 1em; vertical-align: -0.25em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathcal\" style=\"margin-right: 0.02778em;\">O</span><span class=\"mopen\">(</span><span class=\"mord\">1</span><span class=\"mclose\">)</span></span></span></span></span>.</p>\n</li>\n</ul></div><span style=\"font-size: 0px; line-height: 0;\"> </span></div>"}